President Trump delivered remarks at the Shell Pennsylvania Petrochemicals Complex in Monaca, Pennsylvania. He praised the workers and unions in the energy and construction industries, and highlighted the growth of American energy production under his administration. He criticized the Green New Deal and vowed to protect American energy and jobs. He also emphasized the importance of American energy independence and dominance, and thanked Shell for signing the Pledge to America's Workers to provide enhanced career opportunities. The President concluded by expressing his pride in the American workers and his commitment to their success.